<div type="definition">
<p>BAD in APPEARANCE when SEEN.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current standard word for ugliness and despicability is è 惡 (ant. měi 美 "attractive").</p>
<p>2. Chǒu 醜 (ant. hǎo 好 "handsome") refers specifically to physical unsightliness and does not necessarily connote a general negative judgment on what is unsightly.</p>
<p>3. Chī 蚩 / 媸 (ant. yán 妍 "attractive") refers primarily to the ugliness of human faces, but the word also has more general and abstract uses where it refers to anything unsightly.</p>
        </div>
